packageMeta.name: purescript-string-parsers
packageMeta.description: A parsing library for parsing strings

modules.name: Text.Parsing.StringParser
modules.comments: This module defines the `Parser` type of string parsers, and its instances.

declarations.comments: A position in an input string.
declarations.title: Pos

declarations.comments:
Strings are represented as a string with an index from the
start of the string.

`{ str: s, pos: n }` is interpreted as the substring of `s`
starting at index n.

This allows us to avoid repeatedly finding substrings
every time we match a character.
declarations.title: PosString

declarations.comments: The type of parsing errors.
declarations.title: ParseError

declarations.comments:
A parser is represented as a function that, when successful, returns
a result and the position where the parse finished or, when it fails,
a ParserError with more information on where and why it failed.
See also `printParserError`.
declarations.title: Parser

declarations.comments:
Run a parser, allowing the caller to define where to start within the
input `String` and what to do with the unchanged output of the Parser.
See `runparser` for more typical usages.
declarations.title: unParser

declarations.comments:
Run a parser for an input string. See also `printParserError`
and `unParser` for more flexible usages.
declarations.title: runParser

declarations.comments: Prints a ParseError's the error message and the position of the error.
declarations.title: printParserError

declarations.comments: Fail with the specified message.
declarations.title: fail

declarations.comments:
In case of error, the default behavior is to backtrack if no input was consumed.

`try p` backtracks even if input was consumed.
declarations.title: try

modules.name: Text.Parsing.StringParser.CodePoints
modules.comments:
Primitive parsers for strings, parsing based on code points.

These functions will be much slower than the `CodeUnits` alternatives, but
will behave correctly in the presence of Unicode characters made up of
multiple code units.
